<dl id="n12115f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12115f">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12115f"> 115(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> make act of contrition ~ <small>Orange</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n12115f"><li>FW 81.27 </li><li><a href="../../flex/d/lexd.htm#n12115f">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/d/l39d.htm#n12115f">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n12115f">MS BL 47472-158</ms> </li><li>JJA 46:034 <a name="d1A3d" href="../../ff/fdra/dda.htm#d1A3d">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/d/d1A3d.htm#n12115f">Draft: I.4&sect;1A.3</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">MONAGHAN BANK RAID. APPEAL BY CONVICTED MEN. &hellip; In this particular case an officer said to one of the prisoners: &ldquo;If you don&apos;t tell who robbed the bank we will plug you,&rdquo; and &ldquo;<mark>Make an act of contrition</mark>,&rdquo; and &ldquo;If you don&apos;t tell, your pudding is cooked.&rdquo; The prisoner was put in fear and terror of death when he made the alleged confession, and, consequently, it was not legally admissible in evidence. <small> <a name="IT22aug24" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#IT22aug24"><cite title="source">Irish Times</cite></a> (22 August 1924) 6/3</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
